Javascript Breath First Search. 

Each queue element will have two array: 
* The first array is the current sequence we have constructed so far. 
* The second array is the remaning numbers from nums. 

For every element of the queue we add a new element for every remaning number. For example: 
if our nums = [1,2,3] and we dequed the following element: [ [1], [2, 3] ], then: 
	We iterate through the second array and add  [ [1 ,2] , [3] ] and [ [1, 3] , [2] ] to the queue. 


```
var permute = function(nums) {

    const result = [];
    const queue = [];

    queue.push([[], nums]);

    while(queue.length){
        const [currentSequence, availableNumbers] = queue.shift();

        if(availableNumbers.length === 0)
        {
            result.push(currentSequence);
            continue;
        }


        for(let i =0; i < availableNumbers.length; i++)
        {
            const number = availableNumbers[i];
            queue.push([
                [...currentSequence, number], 
                [...availableNumbers.slice(0, i), ...availableNumbers.slice(i + 1)]
            ]);    
        }   
    }

    return result;
};
```

