solutions.content:
Least Recently Used 

---

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________

**first of all figure out which Data Structues will help us :**

as we have to perform these functions

1:GET:

       if key is  PRESENT:

               then give the value associate with this this key 

               and this key-value pair updated to  currently used pair

       if key is Absent :
	           return -1

3: PUT:



       if key is  PRESENT :

               update the key value pair 

       if key is Absent :

              if the cache size full

                    then remove the least recently pair and  put current pair 

                else

                    put the current pair

**NOW ,**  we can see that 

1:   we have to keep track of our keys so for this **unordered_map** will help us 

2: as we have to do **ADD, REMOVE , and Update operations .**

   if we take ans **ARRAY**

	  we can do add in o(1) , update in o(1) , but for remove we have to shift all the values after the removed index



   if we take **SINGLY LINKED LIST:**

         we can do add o(1), but for update and remove we need the previous pointer it will take o(N) 

   so we came to an end that ,

         Doubly linked list   with the help of  Maps  are sufficient to achieve an efficient solution.

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Additional functions :

1. **insert_helper :** helps to insert a node in the front of list 
2. **remove_helper:** helps to remove a node from the list;

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________

  **Now move to algorithm:**

1. we create a Doubly linked list with the help of given **key , value.** with two **dummy nodes** as head , tail to keep track starting and ending node of list
2. we create a  unordered map with the key as integer and value as a node of our list 
3. for **PUT** function.

        1:  check in the map if the key is present or not .

               — if the key is present :

                    a: first we remove the node with the help of 

                         remove_helper

                     b: add this removed node in front of list with the help        

                          of insert_helper (insert at front)

                     c: update the the map accordingy.

                — key is  not present :

                       Now check the size of our cache

                        — if the size is FULL:

                                 then we remove the least recently node [which is the previous node of tail as as per our approach]

                                 and add the new node which store the given information.

                        —else 
                                    simply add the new node with the given information.

1. for **GET** function. 

                — check in our map if the required key is present or not .

                          if the required key is present 

                                     a: give the value of required key with the help of map.

                                     b: we also update this node as the recently used for this we simple first remove this node and again add in front with the help of our additionals  funcitons.

                           — if not present

                                     return -1;

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________

```

class LRUCache {
public:

    class node{
        public:
        int key;
        int val;
        node* next;
        node* prev;

        node( int key , int val)
        {
            this->key = key;
            this->val=val;
            this->next=NULL;
            this->prev=NULL;

        }
    };

    unordered_map<int,node*>mp;
    int capacity;

//two dummy nodes to keep track starting and ending point of list  
    node * head = new node(0,0);
    node * tail = new node(0,0);



    LRUCache(int capacity)
    {
        this->capacity = capacity;
        head->next=tail;
        tail->prev= head;

    }

// function to help a node in the next to head [can say front of our list]
    void insert ( node* currnode)
    {
        currnode->next = head->next;                      // adding node in next of head (front of our cache)
        head->next->prev = currnode;
        head->next= currnode;
        currnode->prev= head;
        mp[currnode->key]=currnode;                       //update map accordingly
    }


// function to remove a node 
    void remove(node* currnode)
    {
        mp.erase(currnode->key);
        currnode->next->prev =currnode->prev;
        currnode->prev->next=currnode->next;

    }


    int get(int key) 
    {
       // if key is not present than return -1;
        if(mp.find(key)==mp.end())
        {
            return -1;
        }
        //if key is present , than update the node and return the value associated with the key
        // for update first we remove the node and then add at start of list with the help of insert function
        node *currnode = mp[key];
        remove(currnode);
        insert(currnode);
        return currnode->val;

    }

    void put(int key, int value)
    {
       //if key is already present than we have to update it 
       // similiary we first remove and then add node in front with the help of insert helper 
        if(mp.find(key)!=mp.end())
        {
            remove(mp[key]);
        }

        // if size is full then we have to remove the least recently used node
        if(mp.size()==capacity)
        {
            remove(tail->prev);
        }
        insert(new node(key,value));

    }
};
```


