class LRUCache extends Map {

    constructor(capacity) {
        super()
        this.capacity = capacity
    }

    get(key) {
        if (!this.has(key)) { return -1 }
        let val = super.get(key)
        this.delete(key)
        this.set(key, val)
        return val
    }

    put(key, value) {
        if (this.has(key) || this.size < this.capacity) {
            this.get(key)
            this.set(key, value)
        }
        else if (this.size > 0) {
            this.delete(this.keys().next().value)
            this.set(key, value)
        }
    }
}
```

Explain:
* Keys in JavaScript Map are ordered.
* Override Map `get` method to move the key to the end (delete then set again, O(1) complexity)
* `Map.prototype.keys()` returns an `Iterator` instead of an array, so using `next()` to get the first key is O(1) complexity.
* `class` syntax is cleaner then `prototype` IMO :)

